Published 2025-04-18
—ЩRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2025-04-18-twin0295.mdЩ@95f3da6b72c0b39be115040513105f643399a2730309915160ec9712b1969f81Щ"title: 'This week in Nushell #295'‘ЅHighlights and Special ThanksЪТIt's really, really cool when someone sees a Discord discussion and submits a PR within a few hours to improve things, especially

when it's a (relatively) new contributor. Many thanks to the ultra-cool @Mrfiregem for making 
``kill ...$in``
 work!
Wow! An even dozen PRs for Polars this week, with 10 of these coming from @pyz4! New commands include 
``polars truncate``
,

``polars over``
, 
``polars convert-time-zone``
, and 
``polars replace-time-zone``
. A dozen thanks!
@whiter001 created a new, Nu (newNu?) plugin example ... written in JavaScript?! Nice work!
On a related note, the next time you go looking for plugin examples, keep in mind that they've moved out the main repo.

They weren't paying rent, they were eating our groceries, and they forgot to feed the goldfish. But if you really must know,

here's their 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/plugin-examples] new address
.
Read below for more great contributions, and thanks to the wonderful contributors!
’ђђЪ)Title: title: 'This week in Nushell #295'
Path: Highlights and Special Thanks
Content:
It's really, really cool when someone sees a Discord discussion and submits a PR within a few hours to improve things, especially

when it's a (relatively) new contributor. Many thanks to the ultra-cool @Mrfiregem for making 
``kill ...$in``
 work!
Wow! An even dozen PRs for Polars this week, with 10 of these coming from @pyz4! New commands include 
``polars truncate``
,

``polars over``
, 
``polars convert-time-zone``
, and 
``polars replace-time-zone``
. A dozen thanks!
@whiter001 created a new, Nu (newNu?) plugin example ... written in JavaScript?! Nice work!
On a related note, the next time you go looking for plugin examples, keep in mind that they've moved out the main repo.

They weren't paying rent, they were eating our groceries, and they forgot to feed the goldfish. But if you really must know,

here's their 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/plugin-examples] new address
.
Read below for more great contributions, and thanks to the wonderful contributors!
—ЩRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2025-04-18-twin0295.mdЩ@a12f5ee4dde07cf67c65b42decae81e274d46e26cb17f653020ecee6134466d5Щ"title: 'This week in Nushell #295'‘§NushellЪQpyz4 made several contributions to the 
``polars``
 integration:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15583] loosened constraints on accepted expressions in 
``polars group-by``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15582] added 
``polars truncate``
 for rounding datetimes
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15574] fixed casting as date to return 
``Date``
 type instead of 
``Datetime<ns>``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15570] expanded 
``polars col``
 to handle multiple columns and by types
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15564] updated 
``polars lit``
 to handle nushell 
``Value::Duration``
 and 
``Value::Date types``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15557] updated 
``get-``
 datetime components commands to allow expressions as inputs
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15553] extended 
``NuExpression::extract_exprs``
 to handle records
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15551] added new command 
``polars over``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15550] added new command 
``polars convert-time-zone``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15538] added new command 
``polars replace-time-zone``
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15581] added 
``--raw-value``
 option to 
``debug``
 command
dependabot
[
bot
]
 bumped dependencies:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15580] data-encoding from 2.8.0 to 2.9.0
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15579] rust-embed from 8.6.0 to 8.7.0
ayax79 fixed issues:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15577] cannot find issue when performing collect on an eager dataframe
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15572] output type of 
``polars schema``
blindFS made improvements to LSP and completion:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15576] fixed a panic caused by completion with decl_id out of range
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15567] refactored flat_map with mutable accumulator
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15546] fixed quoted cell path completion
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15536] included decl_id in suggestion_kind for later usage
0x4D5352 made changes:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15575] replaced 
``repeat().take()``
 with 
``repeat_n()``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15568] moved 'job' to the experimental category
jjflash95 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15562] fixed #15440 where 
``default --empty``
 fails at empty streams
Mrfiregem 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15558] allowed spreading arguments of the 
``kill``
 command
cosineblast 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15556] made 
``config``
 commands add frozen jobs to the job table
cptpiepmatz 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15552] added 
``--plugins``
 flag to 
``nu-std/testing.nu``
zhiburt 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15500] fixed commit f25525b
whiter001 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15482] created 
``nu_plugin_node_example.js``
